  <notes>
**Completed 2026-06-18 (Wave D-1 parallel agent for R4-099).**

### Pattern D shape resolution

The audit note's "Calendar shim has zero chrome" was reconciled with the source: Calendar's shim DOES pass `title: "Calendar"` to its `ContentSectionConfig` (calendar.registration.ts:55), which renders via `SectionPanel.titleBar`. The "zero widget chrome" claim refers to the CalendarWorkspaceWidget itself having NO `<PaneHeader>` of its own â€” the SectionPanel title from the shim is the SOLE title bar. SmartTodo previously violated this by having BOTH a SectionPanel title ("My To Do List") AND a widget-internal `<PaneHeader title="My To Do List">`, hence the duplicate-title-bar in the 2026-06-18 UAT screenshot.

Resolution applied: shim provides `title: "Smart To Do"` (mirrors Calendar); widget's `<PaneHeader>` removed entirely and replaced by a single `<Toolbar>` row carrying `[SearchBox, +, Open, refresh]`. The widget's `title` prop survives ONLY for `aria-label` on the root region.

### Implementation summary

**Modified files (3):**
1. `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/todo.registration.ts` â€” collapsed to structural-only shape. `title: "Smart To Do"`; NO `toolbar` prop; `WidgetErrorBoundary` retained; `FeedSyncBridgeHost` simplified (refetchRef field deleted â€” host bus already captures via `ctx.onRefetchReady`). Imports trimmed: removed `Button`, `AddRegular`, `OpenRegular`, `ToolbarDivider` (defunct after toolbar removal).
2. `src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components/src/widgets/SmartTodoWidget/SmartTodoWidget.tsx` â€” `<PaneHeader>` removed; single `<Toolbar size="small" aria-label="Smart To Do toolbar">` added containing `[SearchBox, Add, Open, Refresh]` in that exact order. New state: `selectedId: string | null` (single-select), `searchQuery + appliedQuery: string` (debounced 150ms). New `filteredItems` useMemo for in-memory substring filter against `sprk_name + sprk_description`. Stale-selection guard clears `selectedId` if the selected card is filtered out. Default `title` prop renamed "My To Do List" â†’ "Smart To Do". Card rendering uses `todoCardSelected` class when selected (brand-tinted border + background).
3. `src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components/src/widgets/SmartTodoWidget/SmartTodoWidget.styles.ts` â€” added `toolbar` (sole chrome row), `searchWrap` (flex-grow left half), `toolbarActions` (flex-shrink-0 right half), `todoCardSelected` (brand-tinted selected variant).

**Coexists cleanly with R4-101 (parallel agent for W-3):** the styles file ended up with my 4 classes + R4-101's 6 group-* classes; widget body uses R4-101's `groupedColumns` rendering loop (Today/Tomorrow/Future sections), inheriting my Toolbar + selection state seamlessly.

### Build verification

- `@spaarke/smart-todo-components` `tsc --noEmit`: clean (0 errors)
- `LegalWorkspace` Vite production build: 3,312 modules in 13.51s, single-file 2,252 KB / gzip 623.88 KB (~+3 KB vs pre-099 baseline from R4-101's grouping code)
- `SmartTodo` Code Page Vite build: 3,279 modules in 6.00s, single-file 1,744 KB / gzip 474 KB (R4-101 hook hoist verified end-to-end)

### Acceptance criteria

All 8 criteria PASSED:
1. âś… Shim mirrors Calendar shape (`title` on config, NO `toolbar`)
2. âś… Single title bar ("Smart To Do" via SectionPanel) + single toolbar (`[SearchBox, +, Open, refresh]`)
3. âś… SearchBox debounces 150ms â†’ in-memory filter; clearing restores
4. âś… Open selection-aware (`disabled={selectedId === null}`)
5. âś… Zero v8 imports, zero inline styles in our code (R4-101's `borderLeftColor` inline is theirs, documented in their styles comment)
6. âś… Both `npm run build`s clean
7. âś… A11y: `<Toolbar aria-label="â€¦">` landmark, tab order = visual order, `aria-label` on every button, `aria-pressed` on selected cards, `aria-live` on empty/match-empty states
8. âś… POML status `complete` + TASK-INDEX row + header counts updated

